/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:9:1. definable on the suitable-weak / LEI floor,
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:12:4. insertable into an actual endpoint argument after localization and nonlocal pressure debt are paid.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:18:### Step 1 - Freeze one material observable, one solution framework, and one endpoint
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:20:This is the strongest step in the chain because it demands scope control early. But it hides the hardest issue inside the word "admits." For observables like cumulative positive strain or deformation growth, admissibility is not a light bookkeeping matter. On the suitable weak / LEI floor, there is no honest Lagrangian flow map with the regularity needed to define many deformation-based quantities in the way the rest of the chain seems to want. If the branch already expects this, then Step 1 is mostly a kill switch, not a route-building step.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:22:The endpoint choice is also under-motivated. "Local concentration exclusion by default" is not just a neutral default; it is a very specific theorem-facing burden. The chain never justifies why this endpoint is the one most naturally matched to the observable class. That makes the route look pre-biased toward the endpoint inherited from the ambient program rather than the endpoint most naturally supported by transport-side structure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:29:- no compatibility with LEI-level compactness.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:45:This is a reasonable discipline check, but it likely kills the branch almost automatically because "exact" and "coercive" are being demanded from the same object. Transport-flavored observables in Navier-Stokes often give intuition, alignment language, or scenario descriptions, but not one-sided control on the actual bad terms that matter in an endpoint argument. The chain seems aware of this, yet still frames coercivity as if one promoted gain might plausibly emerge after Step 2. That optimism is not well defended.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:47:The term "one named bad term" is too permissive and too vague. A branch can appear to pass this gate by controlling a secondary burden while leaving the dominant obstruction untouched. Without a ranked burden ledger, Step 3 can certify leverage on the wrong target.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:49:There is also a methodological asymmetry here: the route demands strict coercivity from the candidate observable but does not equally demand proof that the baseline burden it compares against is the true bottleneck. That creates a selection bias toward declaring "non-coercive" simply because the branch chose an endpoint ledger where the observable was never naturally competitive.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:55:This is the step where the chain most clearly inherits the ambient program's conclusion pressure. It insists that the gain survive insertion into "one LEI / CKN concentration or stretching line" and that all cutoff, pressure, nonlocality, and temporal-window debt be charged immediately. That sounds rigorous, but it may be rigged against any material observable whose value is inherently semi-global or multi-scale.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:57:In other words, the chain does not only test whether the observable is useful. It tests whether it is useful in one very specific proof architecture. That is not the same question. A genuine transport-side mechanism might require a different localization scheme, a different compactness package, or a different endpoint notion entirely. Step 4 treats failure to fit the inherited ledger as evidence against the mechanism itself.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:59:The phrase "reject gains that control only a trajectory-level surrogate with no endpoint insertion" is too dismissive. If the route's starting point is deterministic material stretching, then trajectory-level or flow-map-level surrogates are not accidental byproducts; they may be the native structure. The right conclusion may be "this branch needs a different theorem interface," not "the gain is illegitimate."
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:80:This step is procedurally fine, but by this point it mostly formats the outcome of earlier gates. It does not add analytical strength. The classification list is useful, though it still blends distinct failure types that should stay separate. For example, "endpoint-transfer failure" could mean:
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:83:- scaling mismatched the endpoint,
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:85:- the endpoint argument required a different topology than the observable controls.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:93:### 1. The chain is too endpoint-inherited
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:95:The route presents itself as transport-first, but its decisive tests are all phrased in terms of insertion into an inherited LEI / CKN-style theorem ledger. That means the chain is not asking "can deterministic material stretching produce a real theorem mechanism?" It is asking "can deterministic material stretching be made to serve our existing proof interface?" Those are different questions. The latter is much narrower and much more likely to fail for structural rather than conceptual reasons.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:122:- or a new endpoint interface.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:138:Those strengths do not rescue the route, though. The chain is best understood as a rigorous demolition protocol for deterministic material-stretching ideas under an inherited endpoint agenda, not as a well-balanced search procedure for discovering a live deterministic transport theorem route.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:142:If the goal is to test whether a deterministic material-stretching observable can be plugged into the current LEI / CKN theorem machinery, this chain is useful and probably well-aimed. If the goal is to discover whether deterministic transport structure contains a genuinely different theorem mechanism beyond that inherited machinery, the chain is too narrow, too pre-filtered, and too biased toward confirming failure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/coupled-energy-helicity-scope-lock/INDEX.md:14:  baseline cash-out, one same-currency gain threshold, and one dedicated exact
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The problem is that the chain still overestimates what "exact packet structure" is likely to buy. Exact helical triad bookkeeping is real, but real is not the same as coercive. Waleffe-style interaction geometry, same-helicity suppression, and decimated-sector advantages have been around for a long time. The hard issue is not whether one can write a packet-complete ledger. The hard issue is whether any sign or exclusion effect survives full mixed-helicity completion, shell summation, localization, pressure restoration, and insertion into an LEI/CKN-facing endpoint. That is exactly where these ideas usually die.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The candidate "bad transfer patterns" are not interchangeable. Comparable-scale stretching production, shell-bridging concentration feed, and similar targets sit at different levels of the problem. One might be natural in helical triad language while another is only natural on an LEI/CKN ledger. Letting the route pick whichever is most packet-friendly invites target shopping.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:21:- The kill condition is too weak. The failure mode is not only "cannot be frozen in one currency." A more likely failure is worse: the chain can freeze everything neatly in one currency that later turns out to be the wrong currency for endpoint insertion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- "Declare what share of the full burden the promoted packet mechanism controls" is correct in spirit and dangerously soft in practice. Unless "share" is quantified against the full nonlinear burden near the target endpoint, the route can certify a mechanism that controls a visually interesting but theorem-irrelevant slice.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:49:### Step 4 - Reconstruct to the inherited endpoint and pay localization debt
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:57:- The phrase "map the packet gain back to one physical-space endpoint line on the LEI / CKN ledger" hides a severe mismatch of levels. A packet gain can be exact and still fail to correspond to any sharp improvement on the local continuation bottlenecks that matter for beyond-De Giorgi.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:58:- If the bad transfer pattern was frozen in a packet-native currency, the conversion to the inherited endpoint may itself cost more than the gain. The route acknowledges this possibility but understates how likely it is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:60:Failure mode: Step 4 shows that the only gains available are symbolic-Fourier gains that evaporate under summation, localization, and endpoint translation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:69:- Tao sensitivity is necessary but not sufficient. An artifact can use exact structure destroyed by averaging and still be useless for the Navier-Stokes endpoint. Distinctness from the averaged model is not the same as regularity leverage.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:79:- The failure taxonomy is too tidy. In reality this route is likely to fail for several reasons at once: prior-art overlap, mixed-helicity collapse, reconstruction loss, and endpoint mismatch. Forcing a single label can understate how overdetermined the failure is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:80:- The final same-currency requirement is better than nothing, but it can create false confidence. Rewriting the conclusion in the Step 1 currency does not mean the route actually paid the exchange costs honestly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:103:### 5. The endpoint mismatch is severe
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:105:The route starts in exact helical packet geometry and tries to finish on an LEI/CKN-style physical-space ledger. That is a major level mismatch. Unless the chain finds an unusually robust invariant that survives this translation, most symbolic gains will be spent before they reach the endpoint.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:122:The honest question is not whether exact helical packet structure exists. It does. The honest question is whether any packet-complete effect survives full mixed-helicity completion and then still has enough one-sided strength left after summation, localization, and endpoint insertion to matter for beyond-De Giorgi. That is a much harsher test, and this chain gives too many opportunities to confuse symbolic exactness with real leverage before that test is passed.
