/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has a serious core idea: kill decorative reformulations early and force any surviving variable package to make contact with a theorem-facing bottleneck. That is a real strength. But the original version is still too discretionary in three places that matter: it freezes the setup too sharply and too early, it does not operationalize the burden ledger tightly enough, and it under-polices prior-art overlap and endpoint insertion debt.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The right repair is not to abandon the chain's anti-repackaging posture. It is to make the screening protocol more reproducible. The refined version should keep the demand for exact equations and endpoint contact, while allowing a small comparison slate, requiring a typed burden ledger, and forcing quantified gain-versus-debt accounting before any positive promotion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:15:Terms such as "estimate-level gain," "same burden currency," and "decorative commutator" are directionally right but not yet decision-ready. The refined chain needs a typed burden ledger, an explicit admissible gain notion, and a rule for when currencies are comparable and when they are not.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:21:The attacker is right that choosing one endpoint and one burden before seeing any exact candidate behavior can manufacture false negatives. The repair is not to remove endpoint discipline, but to permit a tightly bounded endpoint window, for example one primary endpoint plus one backup, before collapsing to a single theorem-facing target.
